tiger-data-app.title: Refactor MediaFlux Client to utilize new Mediaflux::Http requests

comments.body:
@hectorcorrea it is hard to understand which parts of mediflux_client are actually being used and which parts are just copied in from the original spike.  I have converted the methods utilized by the welcome and organization list page, which encompasses many of them.  Below is a list of methods that have not been converted and will no longer work.  Can you identify which one are utilized in y our demo? 
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L44 
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L66
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L104
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L137
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L161
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L193
 * https://github.com/pulibrary/tiger-data-app/blob/4adbf476696f2a0a37f318205679af6735e95341/app/models/media_flux_client.rb#L232

Methods that can be removed:

```
# These were just for testing iterators
def collection_iterate
def collection_iterate_next

# These came from the original spike -- we are not really using them now
def get_content
def upload
```

Methods that we want to keep (they are called from the Project model):
```
def add_new_files_to_collection
def namespace_create
dev namespace_collection_assets
```

There is a bunch of other "newer" methods in the MediaFluxClient class that we want to keep for now and eventually we'll refactor them into a more cohesive API (e.g. `namespace_describe_by_name` and `namespace_describe`). 

The same goes for the `http_post` method on that class, it has a lot of weird logic to handle the upload process, which we are not going to need soon, and we'll eventually want to rewrite and/or ditch.
